This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   Read `prompt.md` describing the MHPCO Claim Office kata and implement a full TDD solution using the Red-Green-Refactor cycle with mandatory skill invocations (test-list, red, green, refactor). The system provides `quote` (compute insurance premium) and `claim` (process damage) operations for magical items (swords, amulets, staves, potions, components). Implementation must be TypeScript with Vitest, CLI entry at `src/cli.ts`. Operating in autonomous experiment mode (no human-in-the-loop between phases).

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Test-Driven Development: strict Red-Green-Refactor cycle, one test at a time
   - TypeScript + Vitest (pnpm test / npx vitest run)
   - APP (Absolute Priority Premise) mass calculation: constants×1, bindings×1, invocations×2, conditionals×4, loops×5, assignments×6
   - Four Rules of Simple Design (priority): Tests Pass → Reveals Intent → No Duplication → Fewest Elements
   - Premium modifiers: item-specific (cursed +50%, high-enchantment ≥5 +30%) applied to item base; policy-wide (loyalty ≥2yr -20%, first-insurance +10%, follow-up -15%) applied to unmodified policy base; processing fee +5G always last
   - Rounding: premiums round up (Math.ceil), payouts round down (Math.floor)
